window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Big. Brash. Barbaric. Who says a troll can’t be the hero?</b></p> <p>Chad has always been quick-witted, a master of the art of trolling. After he loses his cool in a publicly televised stream, he finds himself facing 30 days of full-immersion therapy in the virtual world of Mythos.</p> <p>At first, it seems like a dream come true—a chance to experience cutting-edge technology and escape the consequences of his actions. That is until he learns he’ll be forced to play as a forest troll, a long-hated race in Isle of Mythos.</p> <p>To makes matters worse, the rehabilitation program features a cast of convicts, each with a chance to forge their own path of redemption—some more twisted than others.</p> <p>With a target on his back, Chad finds refuge in the only place that will take him in.</p> <p>He discovers that there's more to troll society than meets the eye. Among these so-called monsters, he finds something he never expected—a tribe to call his own.</p> <p>And learning to channel his barbarian rage might be all that stands between them and extinction.</p> <p><b>Pick up books one through three in this epic fantasy LitRPG series!</b></p>"; 
